	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Safemode</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From The Cataclysm: Dark Days Ahead Wiki</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><b>Safemode</b> (previously: <i>run mode</i>) is a measure to prevent dangerous moves. Active Safemode is indicated with <span style="font: 1em FixedSys, monospace; color:DarkGreen; background:black;">SAFE</span> in the right lower corner of the game screen. When Safemode is on and aggressive <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Monster" class="mw-redirect" title="Monster">monster</a> or <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=NPC" title="NPC">NPC</a> is visible, character will not move without command to ignore nearby enemy (<span style="background-color: #F0F0F0; width: 2em; border: 1px outset #666; border-radius: .3em; -moz-border-radius: .3em; -webkit-border-radius: .3em; margin:0; padding:1px 2px; clear:none; font-family:monospace; font-size:1.2em">'</span>) or turning safemode off. There will be a message like <span style="font: 1em FixedSys, monospace; color:yellow; background:black;">Spotted jawed terror--safe mode is on! (Press&#160;! to turn it off, press ' to ignore monster)</span> . This is to prevent holding down a key and dying before you've realized that something has been trying to kill you.
</p><p>Default <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Key" class="mw-redirect" title="Key">key</a> to toggle Safemode is <span style="background-color: #F0F0F0; width: 2em; border: 1px outset #666; border-radius: .3em; -moz-border-radius: .3em; -webkit-border-radius: .3em; margin:0; padding:1px 2px; clear:none; font-family:monospace; font-size:1.2em">!</span>. Safemode can be restored automatically if Auto-Safemode is on and character does not see a monster for longer than 5 minutes (50 <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Turn" title="Turn">turns</a>). Auto-Safemode can be toggled with <span style="background-color: #F0F0F0; width: 2em; border: 1px outset #666; border-radius: .3em; -moz-border-radius: .3em; -webkit-border-radius: .3em; margin:0; padding:1px 2px; clear:none; font-family:monospace; font-size:1.2em">"</span> key.
</p><p>By default each game starts with Safemode turned on, and Auto-Safemode turned off, it can be changed in the <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php?title=Options" title="Options">options</a>.
</p>
